subSubSection.paragraph:
Eastern Pacific and worldwide distribution . Alaska to the west coast of Baja California and the Gulf of California, Mexico ; cosmopolitan ( Brusca & Hendrickx 2005 ; García-Madrigal 2007 ). Common in temperate and warm-temperate waters around the globe and known as a pan-oceanic species that can be found from the Artic to the Antarctic and all oceans and at depths of 0 to 3000 m (
Vinogradov et al. 1996
).
